“I am proud of my soldiers who are making superhuman efforts to contain the pressure of the enemy … the situation is extremely difficult,” commander Denis Prokopenko said in a brief video message released on Telegram. by Marisol Rifai with Jean-Marc Mojon in Baghdad Iraqi forces seized 15 villages from the Islamic State group Sunday, launching a daunting operation to retake west Mosul which aid groups warned will put civilians in grave danger. April 21 (Reuters) - A top ally of Russian President Vladimir Putin said Russian forces will seize the last main stronghold of resistance in the besieged city of Mariupol on Thursday after Ukraine proposed talks on evacuating troops and civilians there. Russia’s war on Ukraine continues to take a sad toll on Ukraine’s people. Moscow is trying to reorient its attack to at least claim a minimum victory — but that clock is ticking.